author: Werner Diwischek
description: Immutabel EO field configuration will be initalized by @FieldBean object.

creationDate.description: Used to define the creation of an item.

default.description: Set when an default implementation is defined within an interface.

description.description: A description of the model used by every model extending BaseClassImpl.

fieldName.description: A name for different purposes depending on the model.

final.description: If true only a setter for the private variable is generated. When setting a value in an EO context an exception is thrown.

generated.description: Indicates a generated value?! A generated flag for @FieldBean

id.description: The numeric id of an instance of a class.

javascriptType.description: The type of javascript is derived from the java type.

max.description: A maximal length for field string types

min.description: A minimal length for field string types

modelKeys.description: A string representation for a list of modelsConfig.

module.description: Defines a target module where generating occurs.

moduleScope.description: Defines scope of the configuration within module, eg 'test' or 'main' .

override.description: Indicates that a super or interface defines the method already but is overwritten. When java is generated an override annotation is set.

property.description: Indicates that a field is a config property map value which can be implemented as a default interface method.

scope.description: A scope for the cache value.

super.description: Marker to show, that the field is implemented in a super class.

transient.description: Will ignore field when a persistiong occure. Create a transient annotation when java is generated.
